Communicated by:
ProMED
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Data by country, area, or territory for 20 Sep 2021 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2021%20WHO%20Daily%20Tables%20SEPT20_1632248199.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 39.4% of daily case numbers and 38.2% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 88.05 million cases. Brazil reported over 150 000 cases in the last 24 hours, followed by Mexico, while the USA did not report any cases. Three additional countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, while 3 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The European region reported 28.5% of daily case numbers and 28.7% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 68.41 million cases. Many countries not reporting cases in the last 24 hours or longer include Spain, Belgium, Sweden, and Switzerland, among others. Nineteen countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, and an additional 7 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 6.7% of daily case numbers and 9.3% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 15.48 million cases. Iran reported the highest number of cases (15 975) over the last 24 hours, followed by Morocco, Pakistan, Iraq, Jordan, and Libya. Lebanon and Egypt reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The African region reported 1.3% of daily case numbers and 2.0% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 5.91 million cases. South Africa (2281) reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours followed by Ethiopia (958). Botswana, Cameroon, and Madagascar, among other countries, did not report cases over the last 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 13.2% of daily case numbers and 12.8% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 7.97 million cases. Philippines reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours (over 19 000 cases), followed by Malaysia, Viet Nam, Mongolia, Japan, Australia, South Korea, Guam, Singapore, and Cambodia.

- The South East Asia region reported 10.8% of the daily newly reported cases and 9.0% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 42.54 million cases. India is dominant, reporting over 30 000 cases over the last 24 hours, followed by Thailand (12 709), Indonesia (1932), Myanmar (1585), Bangladesh (1555), and Nepal (975). Sri Lanka, and Maldives have not reported any cases for the last several days.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 20 Sep 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

